==English==
===Etymology===
[[Blend]] of '''[[Hong Kong]]''' and '''[[Vancouver]]'''
[[Category:Portmanteaus|hongcouver]]

===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''Hongcouver'''

#(''informal, somewhat derogatory'') A [[nickname]] for Vancouver referring to the [[large-scale]] Chinese Canadian immigration to that city in the 1980s and 1990s, particularly from Hong Kong.

